Format Bridge Privacy Policy
Effective Date:
January 27, 2024
Introduction:
Format Bridge, a file converter app located in New York is committed to protecting the privacy of our users. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.
Information We Collect
We collect a minimal amount of personal data from our users:
Email address: This is optional for users to create an account and receive email notifications. Note: If you sign up with Format Bridge using Apple SSO, we will not have access to your email address.
Converted Files: This is required for us to store your content so it is easily retreivable in our app. We do not collect any other personal data, such as file content.
How We Use Information:
We use your email address solely for: Account creation and management: We need your email address to create and manage your account, including password resets and security notifications.
Data Sharing and Disclosure:
We do not share your personal data with third parties for any purpose, including marketing, advertising, or analytics.
Data Security:
We take the security of your data seriously and have implemented appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect it against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. These measures include: Secure storage: Your data is stored on secure servers with limited access.
Data encryption:
Your data is encrypted in transit and at rest to protect it from unauthorized access.
Regular security updates:
We regularly update our systems and software to address the latest security. vulnerabilities. While we strive to protect your data, no ecurity system is impenetrable. In the unlikely event of a data breach, we will notify you promptly and take appropriate steps to mitigate any potential harm. Your Rights You have the following rights regarding your personal data:
Access: You have the right to access your personal data that we hold.
Correction: You have the right to correct any inaccurate or incomplete data.
Deletion: You have the right to request deletion of your personal data.
Restriction: You have the right to restrict the processing of your personal data.
Portability: You have the right to receive your personal data in a structured, machine-readable format.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
formatbridge@gmail.com
. We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new privacy policy on our website.
You are advised to review this privacy policy periodically for any changes. Contact us if you have any questions about this privacy policy at formatbridge@gmail.com.